01:05.302 --> 01:07.060
Sister?

01:07.062 --> 01:09.380
I don't want to hold you up,
certainly not on your first day,

01:09.382 --> 01:11.060
but about yesterday...

01:11.062 --> 01:12.340
Yes.

01:12.342 --> 01:15.180
None of my other young ladies have
ever asked for a key before,

01:15.182 --> 01:17.900
and certainly none of them have ever
used that tone that you did...

01:17.902 --> 01:19.660
You went through my things.

01:19.662 --> 01:22.222
Someone did.
Can't see Alma or Maude doing it.

01:23.222 --> 01:24.460
Things seemed a little untidy.

01:24.462 --> 01:27.260
I was simply trying to help
put things in order.

01:27.262 --> 01:30.700
All I'm saying is, I hope that
we can put this behind us.

01:30.702 --> 01:31.980
I'm sure we can.

01:31.982 --> 01:33.940
Good. Good. Because there's
absolutely no reason

01:33.942 --> 01:36.700
why you and I should have a problem
with each other, is there?

01:36.702 --> 01:38.502
Is there?

01:41.462 --> 01:42.700
Well, as I always say,

01:42.702 --> 01:45.942
those with nothing to hide
need no lock and key.

01:47.822 --> 01:49.540
Great-Grandmamma.

01:49.542 --> 01:52.220
It has quite a ring to it.

01:52.222 --> 01:53.660
It does, doesn't it?

01:53.662 --> 01:55.380
Certainly put you in a good mood.

01:55.382 --> 01:56.540
Well, many things have.

01:56.542 --> 01:58.660
We'll have to show the baby off to
Libby's family, of course.

01:58.662 --> 02:00.700
Not too soon, I hope.

02:00.702 --> 02:03.260
I wouldn't advise travelling
with a wee one.

02:03.262 --> 02:05.060
I did it with your father.

02:05.062 --> 02:06.060
Very trying.

02:06.062 --> 02:07.740
Just a short trip.

02:07.742 --> 02:09.300
We might even fly.

02:09.301 --> 02:10.539
We could all go!

02:10.542 --> 02:12.340
60 hours in a tin can?

02:12.342 --> 02:13.940
I can think of nothing
less tantalising.

02:13.942 --> 02:16.060
It's the way of the future, Mother.

02:16.062 --> 02:17.860
Yours, perhaps.

02:17.862 --> 02:20.900
Better still, why don't we invite
your parents here, Olivia?

02:20.902 --> 02:22.580
They'll have to make
the crossing some time.

02:22.582 --> 02:24.060
That's a grand idea.

02:24.062 --> 02:25.820
Don't you think, James?

02:25.822 --> 02:26.940
William, too.

02:26.942 --> 02:28.820
He'd love to come.

02:28.822 --> 02:31.460
Late next year.
We'll make it a real bush Christmas,

02:31.462 --> 02:33.743
and by then the baby will be old
enough to be interesting.

02:34.662 --> 02:36.580
Look at you, Granddad.

02:36.582 --> 02:37.662
You're beaming.

02:38.822 --> 02:40.180
I am, aren't I?

02:40.182 --> 02:43.020
Yes, well,
guest lists are a little premature.

02:43.022 --> 02:45.022
We'll see, closer to the time.

